newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia rubber ends mixed on technicals, Tokyo.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia rubber ends mixed on technicals, Tokyo.

text.p: Malaysian rubber prices ended mixed again, with the market virtually untraded on weak consumer interest and a fall in Tokyo futures, dealers said.
"Nothing has basically changed," said a weary-sounding dealer. "The mixed prices are just an adjustment as there's no real buying."
The Malaysian Rubber Exchange and Licensing Board qouted December RSS1 buyer at 321 cents ($1.27) a kg, up 1.50 cents from Monday. December SMR 20 was 1.50 cents lower at 308.50.
Trading houses quoted the SMR CV at 364, SMR L at 343, SMR 5 at 320, SMR10 at 308, SMR 20 at 307 and drum latex at 234.
There were no inquiries reported for Tuesday and buyers did not show any immediate signs of returning to the market, said dealers.
"The weather has also started improving the last two days... so I guess there's no real reason for prices to go higher without buying," said a dealer.
The INRO five-day average rose to 243.98 Malaysian/Singapore cents per kg on Nov 4 from 243.09 on Nov 1. The daily indicator was higher at 245.08 against 244.76.
